{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ac1eb368-9683-43d5-9bf0-876a59351893","content":"Here's what you need to change to upgrade to **MSTest v3**:\n\n### 1. `.csproj` — Replace references with a single package\n\n- **Remove** the old assembly reference (`Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`)\n- **Remove** the separate `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` package\n- **Add** the unified `MSTest` meta-package (v3+), which bundles the SDK, framework, and adapter\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.3\" />\n```\n\n### 2. `.cs` files — No changes needed\n\nYour `using`, attributes (`[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, `[Timeout]`), and `Assert` calls are all compatible with MSTest v3. The namespace `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` is still used.\n\n### 3. Optional but recommended\n\n- **Upgrade `TargetFramework`** from `net462` to `net8.0` or `net9.0` if possible. MSTest v3 works on .NET Framework but you get better tooling on modern .NET.\n\nWant me to apply these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d619403d-ba7d-41a9-b6c3-4a6d01a76c5b","outputTokens":284},"id":"347c0dc6-7186-482d-9f20-ab7fc160ac5e","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:57:19.922Z","parentId":"df296253-489e-47f9-a1c9-e75a67ae3d7d"}
